SIMPLE: parian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parian
<hw>Pa"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Parius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to <etsep>Paros</etsep>,
an island in the Aegean Sea noted for its excellent statuary marble;
<as>as, <ex>Parian</ex> marble</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Parian chronicle</b></col>, <cd>a most ancient chronicle
of the city of <city>Athens</city>, engraved on marble in the Isle of
Paros, now among the Arundelian marbles.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Parian
<hw>Pa"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or inhabitant
of Paros.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A ceramic ware, resembling unglazed porcelain
biscuit, of which are made statuettes, ornaments, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paridigitata</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
